":23.3,"dividend_rate":10.0,"dividend_yield":3.11,"payout_ratio":0.0,"five_yr_avg_div_yield":1.65,"revenue":20780353536.0,"revenue_per_share":127.536,"revenue_growth":0.001,"ebitda":2759396864.0,"ebitda_margins":0.13279,"gross_margins":0.66139,"operating_margins":0.080690004,"profit_margins":0.10428,"net_income":2166961920.0,"total_cash":4251122944.0,"total_cash_per_share":26.135,"total_debt":207123008.0,"debt_to_equity":0.852,"enterprise_value":48185683968.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":17.462,"enterprise_to_revenue":2.319,"earnings_growth":-0.237,"shares_outstanding":162810084.0,"float_shares":48872409.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.69954,"held_pct_institutions":0.07509,"beta":-0.062,"fifty_two_week_high":527.8,"fifty_two_week_low":317.75,"fifty_day_average":371.786,"two_hundred_day_avg":431.6915,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":658.85,"all_time_low":12.4,"long_business_summary":"FDC Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and trades in pharmaceutical products in India, the United States, and internationally. The company offers pharmaceutical formulations for various therapeutic segments, including anti-infectives, gastrointestinal, ophthalmology, vitamins, minerals, dietary supplements, cardiovascular and anti-diabetic therapies, respiratory care, gynaecology, dermatology, and analgesics in the form of tablets, capsules, oral liquids, ophthalmic drops, topical preparations, and paediatric-friendly solutions. It also provides functional food, such as flavoured ORS powders, ready-to-drink electrolyte beverages, vitamin-enriched supplements, antioxidant blends and protein-fortified drinks; and various active pharmaceutical ingredients. The company sells its products under the Zifi, Zefu, Zocon, Amodep-AT, Zathrin, Vitcofol, Ziglim, Ziglim-M,Mycoderm, Zoxan, Cotaryl, Pyrimon DF, Zipod, Electral, and Enerzal brands. It also exports its products to approximately 50 countries. FDC Limited was founded in 1936 and is based in Mumbai, India."}}